The paper proposes a method for unsupervised video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The method also involves similarity measures and instance selection, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also mentions frequency of appearance and trajectory, which are related to statistical learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves object proposals and semantic co-segmentation, which are related to multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves tracking objects, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) the fifth likely sub-category.
